President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama will host German Chancellor Angela Merkel and her husband, Dr. Joachim Sauer, for an Official Visit and State Dinner at the White House on June 7, 2011. This will be the first Official Visit by a German chancellor since 1995. During the visit, President Obama will present Chancellor Merkel with the 2010 Medal of Freedom. The visit highlights the importance of the U.S.-German alliance, the friendship between the two countries, and their commitment to working together on various issues such as Afghanistan, the Middle East, Iran, human rights, and global economic stability.